          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toss the sliced {{apple-eating}} with the {{raisins}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, and the juice of the {{lemon}}. Leave to macerate for 10 minutes. Tip into a sieve and press to remove some of the released juice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble the strudel",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 190°C fan. See the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "filo rolling technique",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpa2cmxq00007gv4tuo6rsv1"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": lay a sheet of {{filo-pastry}} on a clean cloth and brush with melted {{unsalted-butter}}. Layer the remaining 3 sheets, buttering each. Spread the filling across the lower third of the strudel, leaving 3 cm at each end. Roll up using the cloth, tucking in the ends. Transfer seam-side-down to a lined baking tray. Brush the top with the remaining butter.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake 30 to 35 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until the pastry is deep golden. Leave to cool for 10 minutes before dusting with {{icing-sugar}} and slicing. Serve warm with crème fraîche or pouring cream.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
